## intuition
extreme_value_theorem:= Maximum/Minimum theorem:= If $f \in C[a,b]$ then $f$ attains its maximum and minimum

Proof. Denote $M = sup(f)$.

$\forall n \in \mathbb{N} \exists x_n \in [a,b] : \left| f(x_n) - M \right| < \frac{1}{n}$. By Bolzano-Weierstrass theorem, $\exists x_n_k \to c$ as $k\to \infty$. $f$ is continous, so $f(x_n_k) \to f(c) as k \to \infty$. Thus $M=f(c)$, The proof for minimum is the similar, with $\inf f$ 

